	aFatherHeading={`A Father for leaders`}
	aFatherBodyHtml={`<p>Here's what almost no one tells you in the middle of leading: the answer to the weight isn't a better quarter, a bigger win, or finally becoming the leader you think you're supposed to be. The answer is a <strong style="color: var(--color-ink);">Father</strong> — a perfect, holy Father who already loves you, today, results or no results.</p><p>You were not made to carry it all alone, and you were not made to earn your worth by what you produce. You were made to receive love first and lead from the overflow. The One who made you doesn't grade your performance, rank you against other leaders, or love you more on the quarters you hit your numbers. He calls you His beloved child — not the impressive you, not the always-has-it-together you, but <em>you</em>, right now, in the wins and the hard calls and the lonely nights.</p><p>So before you're a CEO, a manager, a founder, a name on an org chart — you are His. Your heavenly Father wants to be the steady presence underneath the weight, the one who says: I see you, I'm proud of you, and there is nothing you could build or lose that would make Me love you more, or less. Servant leadership — the kind that lasts — flows from a son or daughter who has first been loved.</p>`}
