	wordHeading={`His Word will not return void`}
	wordBodyHtml={`<p>You might not feel different the first time you read it. That's okay. The Father's love isn't a motivational boost before the big meeting — it's a foundation, and foundations get built quietly, one day at a time. Every verse you take in is your Father planting something in you that no failure can take and no success can inflate.</p><p class="mt-4" style="color: var(--color-ink);">"My word… will not return to me empty, but will accomplish that which I purpose." <span style="color: var(--color-muted);">— Isaiah 55:11</span></p>`}
	fatherSaysHeading={`What your Father says over you`}
	fatherSaysHtml={`<p>"I know the weight you carry — the decisions no one else can make, the people depending on you, the loneliness you don't let anyone see. And I want you to hear Me underneath all of it: you are Mine, and I love you right now — not the successful you, not the always-strong you. You.</p><p>I'm not keeping score against you. I don't love you more in the seasons you win or less in the seasons you struggle. I made you on purpose, and I called you My beloved child before you ever led a single person. When the choice is too big, ask Me — I give wisdom freely and I never shame you for needing it. You don't have to carry it alone, and you don't have to perform for Me. You just have to come. I'm your Father, I delight in you, and no title and no result on earth can change that. Lead from My love — never to earn it."</p>`}
	prayerHeading={`A prayer for leaders`}
	prayerHtml={`<p>Our Father, we thank You and praise You for these leaders — every manager, executive, founder, and business owner carrying more than anyone around them ever sees. Let them hear Your whisper above the noise of the demands and the weight of the decisions. Let them encounter Your love — not as a performance review, but as a Father's delight — and know they are Your beloved son or daughter, not a producer of results, apart from any win or loss.</p><p>Father, You delight over them whether the quarter soars or the plan falls apart. Steady them in the lonely places, give them wise counselors who point them to You, and carry them through the sleepless nights and the heavy calls when they feel like they're not enough. I pray Your protection over them — from burnout and the idol of overwork, from the loneliness of the top, from imposter fear, from the pride that leads alone, and from the lie that they are only as valuable as their latest results. Guard their hearts and their homes.</p><p>Teach them to lead the way You lead — to serve rather than be served, to walk humbly, to act justly and love mercy. Let them know there is no condemnation in You when they fail, that they are fearfully and wonderfully made, and that nothing — no setback, no loss, no ending — can separate them from Your love. Let them know You, their Father, as their true security, greater than any title or success. And may they wake up every single day knowing they are loved by their heavenly Father, fathered first and leaders second.</p><p>In Jesus' name, amen.</p>`}
