		{ question: `What are good Bible verses for leaders?`, answer: `Mark 10:43-45 (the greatest is the servant), Proverbs 3:5-6 (trust God, not your own understanding), Philippians 2:3-4 (value others above yourself), James 1:5 (ask God for wisdom), Proverbs 11:14 (safety in many counselors), Micah 6:8 (act justly, love mercy, walk humbly), Luke 16:10 (faithful in little), Nehemiah 4:14 (remember the Lord, do not fear), and Joshua 1:9 (be strong and courageous, God is with you) all speak straight to what leaders carry. Read and hear them free in the Father's Heart Bible™ at fathersheartbible.com/read.` },
